  "name": "ethernetPacket::protocol::optional-structure::Init",
  "category": "IP",
  "title": "ethernetPacket::protocol::optional-structure::Init",
  "source": "chm_extract_v15/CANoeCANalyzer/Topics/CAPLFunctions/IP/Methods/CAPLfunctionProtocolOptionalStructureInit.htm",
  "syntax": [
    "long ethernetPacket.<protocol>.<optional-structure>.Init();"
  ],
  "description": [
    "Add a protocol option for a specific protocol to the Ethernet packet. The protocol must support options. Following options are available:"
  ],
  "parameters": [],
  "return": "0 – Success\n-1 – Error",
  "example": {
    "description": [],
    "code": "on key '1'\n{\n  ethernetPacket pkt;\n  pkt.ipv6.Init();// initialize a packet IPv6\n  pkt.udp.Init(); // and UDP\n  pkt.ipv6.fragment.Init();\n  pkt.ipv6.fragment.offset = 100;\n  pkt.ipv6.framgent.flag  = 1;\n  pkt.ipv6.fragment.identification = 0x1234;\n  pkt.CompletePacket();\n  output( pkt );\n}"
  },
